  "texts": [
    "Creating a precise and reliable model for static analysis is challenging due to factors such as unpublished hardware specifications and the complexity of translating documentation into analysis models [11].",
    "Moreover, the limitations of static WCET analysis in capturing the behavior of advanced systems can lead to restrictions in the utilization of current hardware [12].",
    "Numerous case studies in the industrial sector have underscored the difficulties encountered when implementing WCET analysis methods in practical applications [13,14,15,16,17,18].This gap in the analytical capabilities to accurately estimate WCET in the context of modern real-time robotic systems is the primary motivation for this thesis.",
    "Recognizing the limitations of existing methods, this research seeks to explore methods that do not rely on detailed knowledge of the precise architecture of the system or the application.",
    "Specifically, this research is designed to find WCET in a black-box manner."
  ],
